cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about relation extraction (RE) using neural networks, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new approach for cross-lingual RE model transfer based on bilingual word embedding mapping, which involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and embeddings. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as detecting and classifying semantic relationships between entities, which suggests cs.IR as another possible category. Finally, the paper uses a small bilingual dictionary with only 1K word pairs, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a less likely but still possible category.
